OL,4,CAirline removes boy, 4, with autism for
OL,5,Cnot wearing Covid mask
OL,6, A four-year-old boy with autism was
OL,7, removed from a flight in the US after
OL,8, the airline refused to recognise his
OL,9, disability and insisted he should wear
OL,10, a face mask, his mother said.
OL,12,FSpirit Airlines told US media that all
OL,13,Ftheir passengers except those aged
OL,14,Funder two must wear a mask.
OL,16,FUS guidelines say travellers with a
OL,17,Fmedical exemption should not be
OL,18,Frequired to wear a face covering.
OL,20,FThe boy's mother said he loved planes
OL,21,Fand was distraught after being removed.
